<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-01-11T16:14:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-01-11T16:14:00-05:00" n="287" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d287">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 422.11G93/830</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Hartman</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Quito</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-01-11T16:00:00-05:14">
                                    <hi rend="italic">January 11, 1916, 4 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Referring to my cable of October 28, 10 a.m.<note n="3" xml:id="d287fn3">
                                <ref target="frus1915#pg_364">Id., p. 364</ref>.</note> I am
                            informed by the president of the Guayaquil &amp; Quito Railway Company
                            that negotiations for private settlement of differences with Ecuadorean
                            Government have failed.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hartman</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>